Description: Space Coast and Treasure Coast with us as we share tips, activities, and hidden gems for your on-the-water and coastal adventures.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: We provide Pontoon Boats as daily rentals to customers, both locals and tourists. Our pontoon boats seat 12 passengers, (or 11 if they decide they would like to hire a captain to drive the boat). We rent the boats out for 8 hours (full day) for $499.00 plus tax/fees. This price includes fuel, so the customer does not need to pay extra for fuel. Our boats are located in the city of Grant-Valkaria, Florida, right on the Indian River Lagoon at the Indian River Marina. The basic concept of how our business is run daily is a customer will either go on our website and reserve a boat or they will call us by phone and reserve a boat. Currently, we have three boats so they can either rent 1,2, or 3 boats if they are available. From there, the customer will receive an email with a waiver to fill out, along with location directions and helpful instructions. On the day of their rental, they will arrive at the Indian River Marina, along with the rest of their group, where they will be met by one of our staff. Our staff will help them and their group get loaded onto the boat, checked in, and give a safety briefing/instructional overview. The customer will then take the boat until their reservation time is over, in which they will return the boat to the same place they departed from. Our staff will help them get docked safely and unloaded.

Description: Elite Agent Realty started as a concept back in 2010 and eventually incorporated in 2012.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, West Coast, Western US
Full Description: Elite Agent Realty started as a concept back in 2010 and eventually incorporated in 2012. through our ingenuity and ability to keep our company current with the ever changing real estate market we have thrived while others fell to the way side.     Real Estate is a $50 Billion a year industry and 90% of those clients, both sellers and buyers, start their real estate search online. Elite Agent Realty knows the office building has become obsolete. Our virtual business model not only makes sense in today’s internet driven marketplace but also let’s us expand 10x faster than our competition at a fraction of the cost.     This also gives us the ability to target markets that ensure profits for the company and most importantly our shareholders. We look for markets with a minimum 5000 homes sold a year and an average sales price of $600,000 or more. Our goal is to service 5% of any particular market place within 3 years and 15% within 10. With a gross brokerage take home of 1.25% of each home's sales price and a 60% profit margin that’s a minimum $1,125,000 annual profit per team at year three.     Over the past year we have been researching and speaking with some of the most successful agents across the country to developed our new marketing strategy. We limited our initial proof of concept to two weeks. Our focus was on The Tri-Valley area of the East Bay with annual home's sales of 5200 and an average sales price of $918,000. We only touched 25% of the online market and received 81 leads at an average cost of $40.99 per lead. Of those leads we are working 4 Listings and 5 buyers totaling $7.7 Million in sales volume, or $96,250 in Gross Commission Income. Our goal is a 5% conversion rate, but it’s too early in our implementation to get true conversion numbers just yet. That being said even if we get one out of those 81 leads into contract, we are looking at a 222% ROI.

Reelfinatics also posts on its Facebook page, GooglePlus account and Tweets new uploaded media posted by its recreational members and affiliates.  This also aides Reelfinatics' viral marketing approach by boosting its affiliates' reach.  To give every member and affiliate more control over their content, each member has a profile/admin page where they can add photos and videos plus update and delete existing media uploaded to their profile. Affiliates can also update their directory description whenever they want.  Reelfinatics is currently building RFV2.0.  There will be a plethora or new features and functionality. Description: VooDoo Pit BBQ will be the Barbeque restaurant of choice for Las Vegas and wherever it chooses to do business.
Headquarters Regions: Western US
Full Description: VooDoo Pit BBQ will be the Barbeque restaurant of choice for Las Vegas and wherever it chooses to do business. Our food will be chef-crafted, in-house from fresh ingredients produced locally, when possible. Our menu will showcase the skills and care of Louisiana’s rich food culture and will always be influenced by that area’s attention to true food and techniques. Our beer and wine selections will always reflect our commitment to American authenticity. Our food will showcase American farmers and ranchers. Our cocktails will be hand made with care from liquors and mixers that we feel good about. If we can make an ingredient, we will. If we can’t we’ll find a reputable source with a commitment to small-batch or craft production. Our service will be friendly, competent and sincere but never cloying. We will be stitched into the fabric of our community as the place to unwind, relax and enjoy exceptional comfort food and drinks at sensible prices. Our business policies will respect and value our employees; our business relationships will demonstrate a commitment to quality; and our operational systems will generate superior return on investment for our stakeholders. We have put together an investor relations webpage that outlines our company information and business strategy. You can review our material (full business plan and detailed financial model) at your convenience either online (contact for password) at http://voodoopitbbq.com/investors/ or by requesting a hard copy.
Industry Groups: Agriculture and Farming, Commerce and Shopping, Food and Beverage, Travel and Tourism

Full Description: TrueDiligence Public Investigations is a vetting and research firm that verifies credibility, identity, and security of potential clients, partners, and investors. The company’s mission is to protect consumers with quality verifications and investigative services establishing true identity, high credibility, and lasting security between consumers and contractors or professionals. It offers many services, including background checks, vetting interviews, background documentation checks, consumer reviews, price or service comparison, resume verifications, applicant screening, and special or private matters. TrueDiligence Public Investigations was founded in February 2011 and is based in Denver, Colorado.
